%% Journey 4: Export Record Pipeline
%% How every record produced by the engine reaches secondary storage and webapps.

sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant Engine as Engine
    participant Log as Log Stream
    participant ExDir as Exporter Director (Broker)
    participant CExp as Camunda Exporter
    participant RExp as RDBMS Exporter
    participant ES as Elasticsearch / OpenSearch
    participant DB as RDBMS
    participant Search as Search Client
    participant Operate as Operate
    participant Tasklist as Tasklist
    participant Optimize as Optimize

    Engine->>Log: Append record (any ValueType × Intent)

    Note over Log,ExDir: Exporter Director reads from last exported position

    ExDir->>CExp: Record (position N)
    CExp->>CExp: Select handler (83 handlers by ValueType)
    CExp->>CExp: Transform to ES/OS document
    CExp->>ES: Bulk index request (HTTP)
    ES-->>CExp: Ack
    CExp->>ExDir: Update exported position

    ExDir->>RExp: Record (position N)
    RExp->>RExp: Select handler (42 handlers by ValueType)
    RExp->>RExp: Transform to DB model
    RExp->>DB: INSERT / UPDATE (JDBC / MyBatis)
    DB-->>RExp: Ack
    RExp->>ExDir: Update exported position

    Note over ES,Optimize: Webapps read from secondary storage (eventually consistent)

    Operate->>Search: Search process instances
    Search->>ES: HTTP query
    ES-->>Search: Results
    Search-->>Operate: ProcessInstanceEntity[]

    Tasklist->>Search: Search user tasks
    Search->>DB: JDBC query (if RDBMS mode)
    DB-->>Search: Results
    Search-->>Tasklist: UserTaskEntity[]

    Optimize->>ES: Analytics queries (aggregations)
    ES-->>Optimize: Aggregated data
